ting those groups to him are fighting through the city and breaking into the undead tower.<br>
<br>
Two groups of mid-50's can fight through the city.  See <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://home.thezone.net/~dhill/hole.htm">home.thezone.net/~dhill/hole.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> for a good plan for how to do it.  Once through the city you're faced with the tough part, breaking into the undead tower.  Even as overpowered as we were for the last raid we couldn't clear the mobs from the tower fast enough to allow us to move the groups inside as we normally would.  The method we used was to get Brenwyn into the tower (using Invis Vs. Undead) and into the safe spot in the room where Kindle's Ghost spawns, then have her CoH people into that room.  Once there it was just a matter of killing the two revenants in that room (leaving Kindle's Ghost alone, she won't agro), and moving to HSK in the room next door.<br>
<br>
The problem with this approach is that it leaves a group outside the tower dealing with wanderers.  As that group shrinks it WILL eventually be totally wiped out, and you'll need to drag corpses into the tower and rez them.<br>
<br>
I will almost certainly be unable to attend a scheduled raid (my wife was out of town for the last one, and that was the ONLY reason I was able to go).  I'd suggest trying to organize this one as another ranger/shaman/chanter alliance epic raid (I know Adis needs Kindle's Ghost still), and seeing if it can fly that way.  It'll be tough to organize since we just went there and we don't have any rangers left (that I know of) that need to turn in their bowls. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usionach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sionach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#0000FF>(5/6/02 5:15:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: High Scale Kirn</span><hr size=1> Skyrapture of OotBS just got his Shiny Tin Bowl last night, so there's at least one Ranger who'll be needing to turn his bowl in (assuming he's combined all his forages <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  IIRC, Eilen of DS, and Adis &amp; Medimus of OotBS all need Ghost of Kindle, so if we could hang out in the tower for about an hour or so, we could get the kill for all three.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As for the CoH into the tower, I think that'll actually be possible to do *without* a wipeout of the unfortunate last group to be left outside.  If those who were there recall, we were at the top of the slope facing the castle where a couple Elementals, a Golem, and a Flighty Fiend all spawn.  Further down that slope, there is one static Revenant and one Revenant that paths out of the castle and up the slope.  If the groups were to set up at the Revenant spawn point for the CoH in, they'd only have to deal with at most 2 mobs at a time.  The Revenant didn't aggro *up* the hill, so the Elementals, etc., shouldn't aggro down it.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I'm working a lot of overtime, including Saturdays, for the next month or two, which is going to make it harder for me to do a long raid like this.  But, if we were to start it around 7p PST on a Saturday, I could definitely be there to help.  Let me know what date you're thinking of, Gamlak, and I'll do what I can to be there and rally the troops for ya! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugamlak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamlak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#0000FF>(5/7/02 2:21:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   HSK</span><hr size=1> As I mentioned, I am on vacation until p.m. EDT 5/17. Any time we can arrange for enough folks to gather is fine with me. I've never been beyond the swimming hole entrance so it's all new to me.<br>
